public static boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
    while (n != 0) {
        int x = n % 3;
        n = n / 3;
        if (x == 0) {
            return true;
        }
    }
    return false;
}
```
This solution uses a while loop to iterate down to the last digit of `n`, where `n % 3` gives the remainder when `n` is divided by 3. Since `x` is the highest power of 3 that divides `n`, `x` must be 0 when `n` is a power of 3. Otherwise, `n` must be the product of some power of 3 and a non-zero remainder, so we can return `false`.

